Eggs laid free, spherical in shape, white, and ornamented with bulbous processes with attenuated apical parts clearly septate and sometimes bent downward ( Figs. 7, 8 ,
15, 16, 17
). Processes with developed polygonal to roundish reticulation. Processes bases with small projections. Egg shell between processes with scarcely visible radial ridges. Usually egg surface poorly visible, covered with debris particles. Diameter of eggs (without processes): 81.2–91.3 m ; height of processes (about 20 on the circumference of egg): 11.0– 17.2 m , their basal diameter: 8.5–12.7 m .
